2. Aesthetics and Clarity of Visualizations 
📝 Description:
Well-designed visuals improve understanding. This includes using appropriate labels, fonts, colors, legends, and spacing to make charts more readable and engaging.

# Barplot: Survival by Age Group with clean aesthetics
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
sns.barplot(data=df, x='age_group', y='survived', palette='Set2')
plt.title("Survival Rate by Age Group", fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel("Age Group")
plt.ylabel("Survival Rate")
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
✅ Why it's effective: The structured layout, soft color palette, gridlines, and labeled axes help the viewer easily interpret the data.
